      "text": "C3 Racing: Car Constructors Championship, released in Britain as Max Power Racing as a tie-in to the Max Power magazine, is a racing video game first released in December 1998, developed by Eutechnyx and published by Infogrames Multimedia for the PlayStation. The game allows the player to race in 11 locations around the world in a variety of licensed sports cars. It is the follow-up to 1997's Total Drivin.",
